<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-0768 </DOCNO><TEXT>Of all the renewable energy sources, hydropower is the most ancient andmost frequently used source of energy. Wind energy is limited to climaticallyfavoured regions. Solar energy, though utilized on a small scale to fillsome power supply gaps, would be much too expensive for large-scale powersupply in industrialized countries. The author reviews the situationof hydropower, wind and solar power in the Federal Republic of Germanyand attempts a forecast to 2000.</TEXT></DOC>